---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Main from "../../components/Main.astro";
import H1 from "../../components/H1.astro";
import GradientText from "../../components/GradientText.astro";
---

<Layout
        title="bringbackmaps - Restore the Google Maps Button | builtbylukas.dev"
        page="/bringbackmaps"
        url="https://builtbylukas.dev/bringbackmaps"
        keywords="restore google maps, bring back google maps button, google maps extension, fix google search maps, chrome extension for google maps">
    <Main>
        <H1>
            <GradientText>bringbackmaps</GradientText>
            – Restore the Google Maps Button in Search Results!
        </H1>
        <div class="space-y-4">
            <h2 class="text-3xl mb-8 tracking-tight">How to fix the Google Maps button with <em>bringbackmaps</em></h2>
            <div>
                bringbackmaps is a free and open-source Chrome extension that brings the Google Maps tab back to your
                search results, making any location-related searches much easier and time-efficient.
            </div>
            <div>
                <img
                        class="rounded-xl"
                        src="/images/google_search_for_location.png"
                        alt="Screenshot of bringbackmaps extension restoring Google Maps button in search results"/>
                <p class="text-sm mt-4 text-zinc-200">Screenshot: bringbackmaps adds the Google Maps button and
                    clickable map box to search results.</p>
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-3xl mt-8 tracking-tight">How to Use bringbackmaps</h2>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-x-4">
                <div class="space-y-2 w-2/3">
                    <p>Follow these simple steps to bring back the Google Maps button:</p>
                    <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 space-y-2">
                        <li>Install the extension <a
                                href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/bringbackmaps/dhfofnchclaidhjihbikjjemdodddlji"
                                class="underline font-bold tracking-tight">from the Chrome Web Store</a>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click the blue "Add to Chrome" button.</li>
                        <li>Enjoy restored Google Maps functionality for all your location-related searches!</li>
                    </ol>
                    <p class="pt-4">
                        <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/bringbackmaps/dhfofnchclaidhjihbikjjemdodddlji"
                           target="_blank"
                           class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-400 to-rose-600 text-white font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out hover:scale-105">
                            Download Now
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="w-1/3">
                    <img
                            src="/images/bringbackmaps-logo-full.png"
                            alt="bringbackmaps Chrome extension logo"
                            class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl"/>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-3xl mt-8 tracking-tight">Features of bringbackmaps - a Google Search chrome extension
                    for Maps</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>Restores the Google Maps tab to search results.</li>
                    <li>Makes the map box clickable for easy navigation.</li>
                    <li>100% free and open-source – no fees, no ads, no collected data</li>
                    <li>Lightweight and easy to install.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
                <h2 class="text-3xl mt-8 tracking-tight">Privacy Guaranteed</h2>
                <p>Your privacy is our top priority. <em>bringbackmaps</em> does not collect, store, or share any of
                    your data. Everything is executed locally; none of your data is sent anywhere! <strong>All of our
                        functionality happens inside of your browser.</strong></p>

                <h2 class="text-3xl mt-8 tracking-tight">Open-Source and Transparent</h2>
                <p>Curious about how it works? Check out the source code on GitHub:</p>
                <p>
                    <a href="https://github.com/lukas-karsch/bringbackmaps" class="underline">https://github.com/lukas-karsch/bringbackmaps</a>
                </p>
                <p>Or read the related blog article on how this extension was built: <a
                        href="blog/chrome-extension-for-maps" class="underline">Building a Chrome Extension to restore
                    the Google Maps Tab</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </Main>
</Layout>
